        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 10:22AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 1022 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of showers and
isolated thunderstorms extending from near Mandeville to near
Lisbon, or extending from 7 miles northeast of Texarkana to 9 miles
west of El Dorado, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Texarkana, Hope, Nashville, Prescott, Mineral Springs, Emmet,
Blevins, Perrytown, Rosston, Tollette, Fulton, Washington, Bluff
City, Saratoga, Mandeville, McCaskill, Ozan, Cale, McNab and
Oakhaven.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
